President Obama released a statement expressing his sadness over the passing of Kam Kuwata, a friend and political strategist. He praised Kuwata's brilliance in political strategy and his passion for the country and democratic process. The President also mentioned the important role Kuwata played in planning the 2008 Convention, which captured the spirit of their campaign. He sent his condolences to Kuwata's extended family of friends and to those in California who are mourning his loss.